ndi, because no one cares enough to race to vindi since he spawns every eight hours.<br>
<br>
Rogg, your notion on the convention for race mobs is not correct.  It has always been done exactly like SoY handled this matter.  When two guilds race for one mob the first guild there is given the first shot. The second guild forms up, buffs, ect. behind (out of sight) but definitely not out of the zone.  If the first guild fails then the second guild takes the kill. Furthermore, as much as both you and I wish it was not, putting &quot;pressure&quot; on the guild in front of you is both an accepted (if not openly) an effective way of tipping the odds in your favor.<br>
<br>
In all honesty, Soy really hasn't done anything that hasn't been done a thousand times over on this server.  That is not to say that it was a chummy thing to do, because it never is.  I just don't feel that they should be singled out and crucified for doing the exact same thing that nearly every larger guild on this server has done.<br>
