<br>
I have been reading this post since the first page, and I can honestly say that it deeply saddens me.  First, I will say that it saddens me not as much because it is my guild being attacked here, but because of all the childish attitudes flowing.  Obviously people on these boards have little to do more than sit by and humor themselves at someone else’s expense.  It is so horrible how using this game we can hide behind a facade of anonymity. <br>
<br>
I am a proud member of Shadows of Yamabushi.  I have been a proud member since early on in the Yamabushi Clan days.  I can assure you that I believe in honor and truth completely.  I would not dare do something to someone else intentionally to cause them harm or pain.  I am speaking for myself as I am not an officer of any kind in Shadows of Yamabushi, but I would like to say that I apologize for any perceived wrong doing by the guild I am a member of.  I cannot speak for any other single member when I make that statement, but I promise you that if you have a problem with Shadows of Yamabushi you can always give me a tell in game.  I cannot guarantee that I can do much about anything, but I will most certainly talk the situation over with you and do my best to see that the situation is resolved.  <br>
<br>
As for the matter with Champions of Norrath, I am deeply sorry.  I was there on that evening, and I participated in the extermination of the Vindicator.  Whether or not Shadows of Yamabushi was in the complete wrong or right is irrelevant to me.  What is relevant is that the actions I participated in have had adverse effects on another very respectable group of people.  For that I apologize.  <br>
<br>
The only thing I have to ask would be for everyone to please take a step back and analyze this.  Is this thread doing anything to foster the community that everyone supposedly wants to build and continue on this server?  I don't think so.  The points have been made on both sides of the fence.  What this thread has turned into is a very large attack on individual people.  Several of these individuals have absolutely nothing to do with the topic at hand.  <br>
<br>
If there was a lesson to be learned by this I can assure you that it has already been recognized.  I am sure that Shadows of Yamabushi will make an asserted effort to communicating better with other guilds when interaction is needed. I would be willing to bet that Champions of Norrath will do the same.  <br>
<br>
It is a sad fact that Vindicator fell under bad circumstances.  Is there anything that can be done...I don't really thinks so.  I have tried and tried, but my darn click stick just doesn’t like to work on NPCs. What can be done is for everyone to move on and to learn from their previous actions.<br>
<br>
I am not going to speak on anyone’s behalf or attempt to defend any individual here for two reasons.  1.  They are old enough to defend themselves and 2. It is absolutely ridiculous that something that most of us think of as an entertaining leisure activity has to be turned into something painful and spiteful.<br>
<br>
I wish you all luck in your adventures in this world, and if you ever see this little smurf looking character that has a striking resemblance to barney, please give me a tell, I love to talk with people and have everyone admire my devastatingly striking exterior.  And if any of you ladies ever feel lonely, I can make an ale that will melt your heart<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
Harammer Vitadonare<br>
